    <h3>Javascript</h3>
    <p>Javascript is a programming language used to implement the interactive portions of the website. i.e. maps, timely updates, </p>
 

    <h3>Operators</h3>
    <p> Note that the code in your web documents is generally loaded and executed in the order 
        it appears on the page. Errors may occur if JavaScript is loaded and run before the HTML
         and CSS that it is intended to modify.</p>

    <h3>Dyanmic Vs. Static</h3>
    <p>Dynamic - the ability to update the display of a web page/app to show different things in different 
        circumstances, generating new content as required.</p>
        <p>Static - A web page with no dynamically updating content.</p>

    <h3>Adding Your Javascript file to your html file</h3>
    <p><script src="script.js"></script>    </p>

         <H3>IMPORTANT NOTE</H3>
         <p>Write comments next to your javascript functions. EXPLAIN what the function does</p>
         <p>// I am a comment- for single line comments</p>
         <p>/*
            I am also
            a comment
          */ for multi line comments</p>
         <p>Initial Expression - expression usually initializes one or more loop counters, and can declare variables</p>
           <p>Condition Expression - expression is evaluated. If the value of conditionExpression 
           is true, the loop statements execute. Otherwise, the for loop terminates.</p>
           <p>Statement - statement executes</p>
    
   
